{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Refimprove|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox Artwork | image_file=File:Van_Gogh_-_Landschaft_bei_Auvers_im_Regen.jpeg | title=Landscape at Auvers in the Rain | alt= | artist=[[Vincent van Gogh]] | year=1890 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | catalogue= | height_metric=50 | width_metric=100 | height_imperial=19.685 | width_imperial=39.3701 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city= | museum= [[National Museum Cardiff|National Museum of Art]], [[Cardiff]], Wales }} '''''Landscape at Auvers in the Rain''''' is an oil on canvas by the [[Netherlands|Dutch]] [[Post-Impressionism|post-impressionist]] painter [[Vincent van Gogh]]. Painted in July, 1890, and completed just 3 days before his death, it depicts a landscape at [[Auvers-sur-Oise]], where van Gogh spent the last years of his life. The depiction of the rain with dark, diagonal lines are considered{{according to whom|date=August 2015}} to be inspired by Japanese art.{{Citation needed|date=August 2015}} This was one of Van Gogh's last paintings before his death.
