{{for|the EP by The Detroit Cobras|Seven Easy Pieces (EP)}} {{Italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = Marina 1 1.jpg | image_size = 234px | title = Seven Easy Pieces | alt = Abramović performing [[Bruce Nauman]]'s ''Body Pressure''. | type = [[Performance art]] | artist = [[Marina Abramović]] | year = {{Start date|2005}} | city = [[New York City]] | museum = [[Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum|Guggenheim Museum]] }}
'''''Seven Easy Pieces''''' was a series of [[performance art|performances]] given by artist [[Marina Abramović]] in [[New York City]] at the [[Solomon R. Guggenheim Museum|Guggenheim Museum]] in November 2005.
Although the performance art world traditionally frowns on repeating individual works, valuing their transient, ephemeral nature as intrinsic to their essence, as she aged, Abramović found herself compelled to preserve the performances that influenced her own development as an artist. Angry at seeing so many of the ideas developed in her and others' performances being appropriated without credit, including by commercial enterprises such as advertising and fashion, Abramović committed herself to archiving seven iconic works by recreating or reinterpreting them in ''Seven Easy Pieces'', but only with the expressed consent of each of the original artists or their estates. "There's nobody to keep the history straight," she told the ''New York Times'' in an interview published in early November 2005. "I felt almost, like, obliged. I felt like I have this function to do it."<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2005/11/06/arts/design/06kenn.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0| New York Times, ''Self-mutilation is the sincerest form of flattery'', November 6, 2005]</ref> ''Seven Easy Pieces'' is available on DVD and is considered{{who|date=August 2018}} to be useful for performing arts students who study [[post-structuralism]].
''Seven Easy Pieces'' comprised seven individual works – two of her own and five by other artists – performed on seven consecutive nights beginning on November 9th. They were, in order of performance:<ref>[http://pastexhibitions.guggenheim.org/abramovic/ Guggenheim exhibition web page for ''Seven Easy Pieces'']</ref>
*[[Bruce Nauman]]'s ''[[Body Pressure]]'' (1974) *[[Vito Acconci]]'s ''[[Seedbed (performance piece)|Seedbed]]'' (1972) *[[Valie Export]]'s ''Action Pants: Genital Panic'' (1969) *[[Gina Pane]]'s ''The Conditioning'' (1973) *[[Joseph Beuys]]'s ''[[How to Explain Pictures to a Dead Hare]]'' (1965) *Abramović's own ''Lips of Thomas'' (1975) *Abramović's own ''Entering the Other Side'' (2005)
==See also== * [https://web.archive.org/web/20060209063317/http://newyorkmetro.com/nymetro/arts/art/15228/index.html Interview ''New York Magazine'' - Provocateur: Marina Abramovic] * [http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/theatre_journal/v058/58.2smalec.html Review of ''Seedbed'', ''Theatre Journal'' - May 2006]
